## Creates an analysis in Amazon QuickSight

### Description

Creates an analysis in Amazon QuickSight. Analyses can be created either
from a template or from an `AnalysisDefinition`.

### Usage

    quicksight_create_analysis(AwsAccountId, AnalysisId, Name, Parameters,
      Permissions, SourceEntity, ThemeArn, Tags, Definition)

### Arguments

<table>
<colgroup>
<col style="width: 35%" />
<col style="width: 65%" />
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr class="odd">
<td><code
id="quicksight_create_analysis_:_AwsAccountId">AwsAccountId</code></td>
<td><p>[required] The ID of the Amazon Web Services account where you
are creating an analysis.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class="even">
<td><code
id="quicksight_create_analysis_:_AnalysisId">AnalysisId</code></td>
<td><p>[required] The ID for the analysis that you're creating. This ID
displays in the URL of the analysis.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class="odd">
<td><code id="quicksight_create_analysis_:_Name">Name</code></td>
<td><p>[required] A descriptive name for the analysis that you're
creating. This name displays for the analysis in the Amazon QuickSight
console.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class="even">
<td><code
id="quicksight_create_analysis_:_Parameters">Parameters</code></td>
<td><p>The parameter names and override values that you want to use. An
analysis can have any parameter type, and some parameters might accept
multiple values.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class="odd">
<td><code
id="quicksight_create_analysis_:_Permissions">Permissions</code></td>
<td><p>A structure that describes the principals and the resource-level
permissions on an analysis. You can use the <code>Permissions</code>
structure to grant permissions by providing a list of Identity and
Access Management (IAM) action information for each principal listed by
Amazon Resource Name (ARN).</p>
<p>To specify no permissions, omit <code>Permissions</code>.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class="even">
<td><code
id="quicksight_create_analysis_:_SourceEntity">SourceEntity</code></td>
<td><p>A source entity to use for the analysis that you're creating.
This metadata structure contains details that describe a source template
and one or more datasets.</p>
<p>Either a <code>SourceEntity</code> or a <code>Definition</code> must
be provided in order for the request to be valid.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class="odd">
<td><code
id="quicksight_create_analysis_:_ThemeArn">ThemeArn</code></td>
<td><p>The ARN for the theme to apply to the analysis that you're
creating. To see the theme in the Amazon QuickSight console, make sure
that you have access to it.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class="even">
<td><code id="quicksight_create_analysis_:_Tags">Tags</code></td>
<td><p>Contains a map of the key-value pairs for the resource tag or
tags assigned to the analysis.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class="odd">
<td><code
id="quicksight_create_analysis_:_Definition">Definition</code></td>
<td><p>The definition of an analysis.</p>
<p>A definition is the data model of all features in a Dashboard,
Template, or Analysis.</p>
<p>Either a <code>SourceEntity</code> or a <code>Definition</code> must
be provided in order for the request to be valid.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
